HEADWORD: Tubinares
<hw>Tu`bi*na"res</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>tubus</ets> tube + <ets>nares</ets> the nostrils.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A tribe of sea birds comprising the petrels,
shearwaters, albatrosses, hagdons, and allied birds having tubular horny
nostrils.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

